reviews.review_text: St. Stephen!! First St. Stephen since 10-31-1971!! Of course the '76/'77 Stephen's are very laid back, almost like they were all on qualludes. But at least they brought it back, if only for a while.

SAINT STEPHEN yeah, jerry bitches about the unplayability of st stephen in an interview from, i think, '81.  but it's lovely to hear.  gets in your head and stays there.  this is a nice show - i've been more into audience recordings lately, mainly because of their shortcomings - cut-outs, leshbombs, people singing along.  endearing and markedly historical. i like a slower eyes of the world, and i like a jumpier scarlet begonias.  but i'll listen to the whole show - certainly not time wasted.

40 minutes Of BLISS - St.Stevie thru Let it Grow happens to be, IMO, one of the most enjoyable 40 minutes of must ever produced by humans on this planet!

Overall, one of my favorite shows, period.

Top-notch quality sound on this aud. 

Listening to the jam on Stevev now and as usual, I cant help grooving in my chair 'til it becomes too confining, then getting up and dancing around like a fool!!!!

WATCH OUT!!  DANGEROUS DANCER!!!!
